<subSubSection pageId="157" pageNumber="158" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="157" pageNumber="158">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="157" pageNumber="158">
Inhabits the lowland evergreen forests and evergreen foothill forests of the Amazon region from 330-1100 m a.s.l. In the Andean region, this species was recorded in montane cloud forests between 1900-2300 m a.s.l. The majority of specimens were collected manually; however, 
<bibRefCitation author="Gillett, CP" journalOrPublisher="Insecta Mundi" pageId="268" pageNumber="269" pagination="1 - 8" title="Distribuccion and biology of the rare scarab beetle Megatharsisbuckleyi Waterhouse, 1891 (Coleoptera: Scarabaeinae: Phanaeini)." volume="80" year="2009">Gillett et al. (2009)</bibRefCitation>
reported that some specimens were collected using flight interception traps.
</paragraph>
